&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Delivering the Report&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Delivering the report to the lord, Lionel&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Through the crystal, we could find out about the fairies and the land condition of Larksdowns. The faries of Larksdowns and Weed Ridge are afraid of the same thing.

There is something dreadful in the Fox Den in the middle of the island. The reason for which the Red Foxes left their cave was the same. Something in the cave, which is unknown to me and even to the fairies of this island. I sense that it has dramatic power and a fearful evil will. This unknown power chased the souls away from the Fox Den and it's surroundings and made monsters without spirit to slaves. Unruled monsters captivated by fear are losing reason.

We, the humans have to do something about it.
Deliver this to to the lord, Lionel.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;I hope this report will change Lionel's mind about these creatures. Do your best.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;A letter from the master of the Divine Association. Okay, I will read it.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></soular007><ac1gt003><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Collect Materials for Armor&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Stone Lizard's Scales&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;Speckled Lizard's Mucus&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;Needle Lizard's Thorns&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;I've seen you quite often lately. Are you a new adventurer in this city? It's good to see the city being lively thanks to newcomer adventurers like you moving around. Moreover, the city's commerce seems to be revitalizing which is good news.

After the&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Did you collect the materials? I need 6 Scales of Stone Lizard, 3 Mucus of Speckled Lizard and 2 Thorn of the Needle Lizard. Don't forget that the Lizards can be easily found at Larksdowns.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Hmm! Good job collecting the materials from the Lizards. The ones you've brought are better than those by other people. Here, the reward I promised to give you.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Collect Materials for Armor&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Stone Lizard's Scales&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;Speckled Lizard's Mucus&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;Needle Lizard's Thorns&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;I've seen you quite often lately. Are you a new adventurer in this city? It's good to see the city being lively thanks to newcomer adventurers like you moving around. Moreover, the city's commerce seems to be revitalizing which is good news.

After the sudden disappearance of the king at the Obsidian Fortress Battles, 5 years ago, the whole nation stirred up and the commerce shrank considerably. Thanks to the merchant union Magistri's effort to stabilize the market we've recovered this much.

By the way, I'm concerned that there are not enough materials for armours and weapons to provide to Kitty and Willy due to the increasing number of adventurers.

In particular, we are running out of Scales of Stone Lizards, Mucus of Speckled Lizard and Thorn of the Needle Lizard, which are used for making armours. If it's possible, collect some of them for me. I will certainly reward you. You can easily find these Lizards at Larksdowns.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Did you collect the materials? I need 6 Scales of Stone Lizard, 3 Mucus of Speckled Lizard and 2 Thorn of the Needle Lizard. Don't forget that the Lizards can be easily found at Larksdowns.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Hmm! Good job collecting the materials from the Lizards. The ones you've brought are better than those by other people. Here, the reward I promised to give you.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></ac1gt003><ac1gt004><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
