&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Managing stat points)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Managing all stat points&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;You are now armed. The next step is to learn how to enter your ability points.

Please click on the face shaped icon above the inventory icon. In the center you can see muscular power, agility, and physical strength etc. with numbers next to it, can't you? Those numbers are your ability points. Next to the numbers, you will see [+]-shaped buttons. By clicking on each [+] button, you can change your ability points.

Each time you go up a level, you can add 3 points to your ability points. So, make sure to adjust your points when level up. The [ability points] box, showing your points is located under the [LUC] sign. Always keep an eye on your ability points.

Well, then, you can now input your ability points as I just explained to you.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;You have not finished yet? You can take your time. It shouldn't take too long.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Your ability points are going up now. The sacred power has now been more engergized. The next step is to register skill books.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></soultu002><soultu003><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Registering Land Skills)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Registering Land Skill Books&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;Usage of Land Skill Points&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;With the weapon armed, I can now explain how to use skills.

When you use skills, you can reinforce your offence more strongly and apply various other different abilities during combat. On the right side, there is a sword-shaped icon. Click on that icon&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;I sell skill books required by the saints. You can contact me if you need other skill books later.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Have you finished? Now finally, you can learn how to use the "Quick-slot"s. This will make it easier for you to use skills conveniently.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Registering Land Skills)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Registering Land Skill Books&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;Usage of Land Skill Points&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;With the weapon armed, I can now explain how to use skills.

When you use skills, you can reinforce your offence more strongly and apply various other different abilities during combat. On the right side, there is a sword-shaped icon. Click on that icon to open the skill menu box. The shortcut to open the skill menu box quickly is the K key on the keyboard.

Now, open the inventory menu box. You can find [Magic Text of Healing Hands (For Training)], which I gave to you. Drag the mouse to this skill book and right-click.

As the book disappears from the inventory, the skill shown in the book will be registered in the skill menu box. There is a [+] button next to the registered skill's icon. When you press this button, the skill will go up to the next skill level. Each skill will cost 1 skill point or more to enable you to use it. Make sure to keep this in mind.

As you advance level by level, you will earn 1 skill point per level. Always check the points when you go up a level. Remember this carefully.

Now then, familiarize youself with using skills.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;I sell skill books required by the saints. You can contact me if you need other skill books later.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Have you finished? Now finally, you can learn how to use the "Quick-slot"s. This will make it easier for you to use skills conveniently.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></soultu003><soultu005><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Registering Quick-slots)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Registering Land Skills in Quick-slot&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;Registering potions in Quick-slot&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Now I will explain how to use skills inside the Quick-slot.

At the bottom right of the game screen, you can see square boxes. Those are Quick-slots. After entering skills in the Quick-slot squares, you can use these skills by pressing the skill number&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;There wouldn't be any wounded people inside the village. So if you would like to try out healing skills, I recommend to go out to the field to help the wounded there.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Have you finished trying out your skills? Then, we can prepare to move on to the sea.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Registering Quick-slots)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Registering Land Skills in Quick-slot&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;Registering potions in Quick-slot&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Now I will explain how to use skills inside the Quick-slot.

At the bottom right of the game screen, you can see square boxes. Those are Quick-slots. After entering skills in the Quick-slot squares, you can use these skills by pressing the skill number in the square on your keyboard. You can also enter items dragged from the inventory into Quick-slots and use them.

In the inventory menu box, I gave you a [Minor Tutorial Powder]. Now drag a potion to the Quick-slot to enter it into a Quick-slot square.

After you entered the second potion into the Quick-slot square, we can start the preparation to move onto the sea.

So, now enter skills and items into Quick-slots, and let me know, when you are done.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;There wouldn't be any wounded people inside the village. So if you would like to try out healing skills, I recommend to go out to the field to help the wounded there.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Have you finished trying out your skills? Then, we can prepare to move on to the sea.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></soultu005><soultu006><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Mini-map reading)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Chat with Stephen&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;You shouldn't have any problems with inland combats now. But Sea Battle is also very important in Florensia. You need a ship to explore the sea. Well, go to the shipyard.

While you did try out your skills, I've contacted Stephen, who is the owner of th&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;You are not there yet? Stephen is waiting. So, hurry! He is not an easy-going person.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;A-ha, you are the one Jaime has mentioned.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Mini-map reading)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Chat with Stephen&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;You shouldn't have any problems with inland combats now. But Sea Battle is also very important in Florensia. You need a ship to explore the sea. Well, go to the shipyard.

While you did try out your skills, I've contacted Stephen, who is the owner of the shipyard. Stephen is now expecting you.

You don't know where to find Stephen? Press M on the keyboard. This will show you the map of Roxbury village. On the map, yellow dots are villagers. Drag the mouse onto each dot to see their names. Stephen should be on the right side of the south port.

Stephen has been waiting for you for some time now. So, go to him quickly.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;You are not there yet? Stephen is waiting. So, hurry! He is not an easy-going person.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;A-ha, you are the one Jaime has mentioned.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></soultu006><soultu007><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Registering a Warship Frame)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Registering warship frame&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;You want to explore the sea? You are very enthusiastic... That's good&amp;#x2026; So we should start the preparations for your sea-adventures, right?

This must be the first time for you to build a ship. So pay attention and follow my instructions carefully!

Fi&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Once the frame is registered, you can't break it down to change it. It will actually be discarded. So choose the one you need carefully.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Have you finished? You are not just enthusiastic, you also have a good eye for this.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Registering a Warship Frame)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Registering warship frame&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;You want to explore the sea? You are very enthusiastic... That's good&amp;#x2026; So we should start the preparations for your sea-adventures, right?

This must be the first time for you to build a ship. So pay attention and follow my instructions carefully!

First, close the chat box, and click on me. This will bring up the [Dock] button. Then click on the [Dock] button. You will arrive at the [Dock], where you can assemble ships.

On the right side of the [Dock] screen, there is the inventory, and on the same side you will find a ship shaped [Small Tutorial Guard Frame]. This is my present to you for having such a high enthusiasm.

Drag the mouse (inside the dock screen) to the Small Guard Frame (top) and right click on it. When a question pops up, asking you "Do you want to register the [Small Tutorial Guard Frame] in the [Dock]?", obviously you have to press [OK], all right?

This part might be a bit difficult to do. But don't be scared. Now try to register the battle ship frame, which will form the base of the ship.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Once the frame is registered, you can't break it down to change it. It will actually be discarded. So choose the one you need carefully.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Have you finished? You are not just enthusiastic, you also have a good eye for this.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></soultu007><soultu008><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Warship tuning)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Tuning warship&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;You want to set off? You are obviously over enthusiastic. Actually, I like people like you, hahaha. Unfortunately, the ship can't sail just with the ship's frame.

So, slow down for a moment, and go back to the [Dock] again. When you get there, you will&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Learning new things is never easy. Take your time. You're smart so you will get it very fast, I believe.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Are you finished? Good, good. What is left now is to learn how to load cannon balls. After that, you can set off to the sea.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Warship tuning)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Tuning warship&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;You want to set off? You are obviously over enthusiastic. Actually, I like people like you, hahaha. Unfortunately, the ship can't sail just with the ship's frame.

So, slow down for a moment, and go back to the [Dock] again. When you get there, you will find ship's main body parts that I have given you. Drag the mouse to [S-shaped Small Tutorial Guard Main Sail], [Grade F Tutorial Demi-Cannon], and [Grade F Tutorial Magic Stone], and right click to open these ship's body parts. Then, you will find the [Tuning] button flashing at the bottom. Press the [Tuning] button to finish assembling the warship. When the warship assembling is finished, click the Exit button at the bottom.

Now, start assembling the warship.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Learning new things is never easy. Take your time. You're smart so you will get it very fast, I believe.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Are you finished? Good, good. What is left now is to learn how to load cannon balls. After that, you can set off to the sea.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></soultu008><soultu009><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Loading cannon balls)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Loading cannon balls on battle ship&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;For someone with a lot of enthusiasm, it has taken long enough, hasn't it? Now this is the last one, so just hang in here a bit longer.

When you are moving out in the sea, you will encounter plenty of pirates, as well as sea monsters. To be able to com&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;You can come to me any time, if you need a ship or ship's body parts. I will give you a good deal.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Good job. Now, you can go out to the sea.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Loading cannon balls)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Loading cannon balls on battle ship&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;For someone with a lot of enthusiasm, it has taken long enough, hasn't it? Now this is the last one, so just hang in here a bit longer.

When you are moving out in the sea, you will encounter plenty of pirates, as well as sea monsters. To be able to combat them, you must know how to load cannon balls.

Cannon balls can be simply loaded in the inventory, similar to your weapons.

First, click the inventory icon to open the inventory menu box. Ah-ha, you forgot which one it is, didn't you? It's the bag-shaped icon on your right.

Now, in the inventory menu box, you will find [Small-sized Metallic Shot for Training]. Drag the mouse to [Small-sized Metallic Shot for Training], and right-click. After doing this, the menu box will change into the battle ship, showing the cannon ball loaded over the left side. You were surprised because the inventory menu box was changed suddenly? Don't worry about that. You can see loaded weapons for the warship or for the character, whenever you click the [Land&amp;lt;-&amp;gt;Sea] icon on the right center of the inventory menu box.

Now try it.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;You can come to me any time, if you need a ship or ship's body parts. I will give you a good deal.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Good job. Now, you can go out to the sea.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></soultu009><soultu010><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Sea Skills)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Chat with Jaime&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Wait a minute! There exist a lot of skills, that you can use only on the sea. Do you know about them? You don't know? Well, Jaime must have forgotten to tell you about it...

Without learning Sea Skills, you can't use the Magic Stone, even when it is lo&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Hahaha. I think I have done everything I am supposed to do. Now go back to the Divine Association master, Jaime.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Sea Skills? Oh dear&amp;#x2026; my apologies. I forgot about them.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Sea Skills)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Chat with Jaime&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Wait a minute! There exist a lot of skills, that you can use only on the sea. Do you know about them? You don't know? Well, Jaime must have forgotten to tell you about it...

Without learning Sea Skills, you can't use the Magic Stone, even when it is loaded on the warship. Now go back to Jaime and learn how to use Sea Skills.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Hahaha. I think I have done everything I am supposed to do. Now go back to the Divine Association master, Jaime.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Sea Skills? Oh dear&amp;#x2026; my apologies. I forgot about them.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></soultu010><soultu011><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Registering Sea Skills)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Registering Sea Skills&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;Usage of Sea Skill Points&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Using Sea Skills is similar to using Land Skills as you already learned. So, we can do this quickly. First, open the skill menu box, and then open the inventory menu box.

You will find [Directory of Quick Cannonade (For Training)], which I have given t&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Uhm, is it difficult? I hope you can learn this quickly, so that you can go out to the sea quickly.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Did you finish it? You did well. When you go out to the sea, you can now sail around nearby coastal waters. Now, finally, I will show you how to sail the ship out to the sea.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Registering Sea Skills)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Registering Sea Skills&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;Usage of Sea Skill Points&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Using Sea Skills is similar to using Land Skills as you already learned. So, we can do this quickly. First, open the skill menu box, and then open the inventory menu box.

You will find [Directory of Quick Cannonade (For Training)], which I have given to you. When you right-click on it, the skill book will disappear from the inventory, and the [Quick Cannonade] skill will be registered in the Sea Skill box.

There is a [+] button next to the registered skill's icon. When you press this button, the skill will go up to the next skill level. Each sea skill as well will cost 1 skill point or more to enable you to use it. Make sure to keep this in mind. As you gain level by level, you will earn 1 skill point per level. Always check the points each time you go up a level. Remember this carefully.

Now then, familiarize yourself with using sea skills.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;Uhm, is it difficult? I hope you can learn this quickly, so that you can go out to the sea quickly.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Did you finish it? You did well. When you go out to the sea, you can now sail around nearby coastal waters. Now, finally, I will show you how to sail the ship out to the sea.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></soultu011><soultu013><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Setting off to the sea)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Chat with Ash&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Down near the wharf in southern Roxbury, you can see Ash. When you engage Ash for a chat, you will find the [Port] button at the bottom of the menu box. If you press this button, you can get to the port, where you can set off to the sea anytime you want.\&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;The world is not yet as clean as we think. If you have any problems on the island, you can come to see me.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;You want to go out to the sea? Click the [Port] button.
And this is your souvenir for finishing this starter-quest completely.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;Start of the Adventure (Setting off to the sea)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Chat with Ash&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Down near the wharf in southern Roxbury, you can see Ash. When you engage Ash for a chat, you will find the [Port] button at the bottom of the menu box. If you press this button, you can get to the port, where you can set off to the sea anytime you want.

Goodbye. If you need skill books or quests, you can always visit me.&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;The world is not yet as clean as we think. If you have any problems on the island, you can come to see me.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;You want to go out to the sea? Click the [Port] button.
And this is your souvenir for finishing this starter-quest completely.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</newversion></questtextxml></soultu013><evgumac01><questtextxml><oldversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;The Shaman plagued by a nightmare (Level 1 ~ 10)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Hand over the Firewood to Magician Puck&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Adventurer, would you spare me just a little of your time? Some time ago, there was a man studying magic in the Holy Union. He maybe made a mistake while he was practicing magical spells.Recently, he was cursed so he keeps having nightmares every single night. This is the first time something like that happened and he couldn't find a way how to solve his problem. He barely slept because of the nightmare. The nightmare is so terrible, so just a few minutes after he falls asleep, he keeps waking up and screaming every night.

We set a bonfire alight by his side to keep the nightmare away. We gave him enough firewood, because we didn't know when we could solve his problem. However, monsters stole all the firewood while he was sleeping. Those monsters ran away to each island and we now need brave adventurers to get the firewood back. Please retrieve the firewood for us! 

NPC Position : Locksdowns - Hill of Sunrise
Target monsters : Fungi, Dodo, Nanani, Ground Parrot, Wild Boar, Devil Walker&lt;/desc&gt;&lt;preDlg&gt;&lt;/preDlg&gt;&lt;startDlg&gt;&lt;/startDlg&gt;&lt;runDlg&gt;We need exactly this kind of firewood, because it is magical and very special.&lt;/runDlg&gt;&lt;finishDlg&gt;Wow! You brought the firewood! Really and truly! Thank you so much. That nightmare was so terrible. Here is a present for you. I am giving you this on behalf of the Holy Union. Thanks. Now I can finally get to sleep a little more.&lt;/finishDlg&gt;&lt;/Questtext&gt;
</oldversion><newversion> &lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Questtext&gt;&lt;Title&gt;The Shaman plagued by a nightmare (Level 1 ~ 10)&lt;/Title&gt;&lt;Mission1&gt;Hand over the Firewood to Shaman Puck&lt;/Mission1&gt;&lt;Mission2&gt;&lt;/Mission2&gt;&lt;Mission3&gt;&lt;/Mission3&gt;&lt;desc&gt;Adventurer, would you spare me just a little of your time? Some time ago, there was a man studying magic in the Holy Union. He maybe made a mistake while he was practicing magical spells.Recently, he was cursed so he keeps having nightmares every single night. This is the first time something like that happened and he couldn't find a way how to solve his problem. He barely slept because of the nightmare. The nightmare is so terrible, so just a few minutes after he falls asleep, he keeps waking up and screaming every night.

